xxl.core.io.converters

Class MeasuredPrimitiveConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.io.converters.Converter<T>
      • xxl.core.io.converters.MeasuredConverter<Object>
        • xxl.core.io.converters.MeasuredPrimitiveConverter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class MeasuredPrimitiveConverter
extends MeasuredConverter<Object>
    This class provides a converter which is able to read and write objects of primitive java type, see JavaType with the built-in measured converters. Information: The MeasuredTupleConverter auto matches Java types and relational types, e.g. VARCHAR and LONGNVARCHAR to java.lang.String using Convert.toJavaTyp() and vice versa using Convert.toRelationalType(). Please note that every type is matched currently but not every relational type can be written or read at this point. If you use e.g. CLOB (JDBC) type the MeasuredTupleConverter will throw an UnsupportedOperationException.

    Note: If you want to use String objects, please consider to use Tuples ( MeasuredTupleConverter) instead of primitive types. That's because String does not have a fixed size which is required.
    See Also:
    Java Types, Use different data types for an index structure, Converter for tuples, Serialized Form

      • MeasuredPrimitiveConverter

        public MeasuredPrimitiveConverter(JavaType type)
        Creates a new converter for objects of type Tuple. A tuple includes a lot of different typed objects. Since a tuple does not know his own object types a description of the data type of the contained objects will be needed here.
        Note: Please check that meta data and tuples match in their object size (dimension)
        Parameters:
        type - A type description of the contained objects within your tuples. You can use objects which implements ResultSetMetaData
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if tupleMetaData is null
